'''Robert Grantshire, 8th Marquess of Winchester''' (1710 - 1763) was a British royal knight and military officer. He was the husband of [[Caroline Grantshire, Marchioness of Winchester]]. 

==Early life==
Robert was born in 1710.

==Knighthood==

==Marriage and children==
In 1739, Robert was introduced to Caroline Pattinson, who had recently been presented to King William. They fell in love and, after six months of dating, they married.

